        <num>CC 3000</num>
        <heading>3000.  Mandatary of both parties</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3000.  Mandatary of both parties
A person may be the mandatary of two or more parties, such as a buyer and a seller, for the purpose of transacting one or more affairs involving all of them.  In such a case, the mandatary must disclose to each party that he also represents the other.</p>
        </content>
